726582f-a.folder: Flushing Avenue & Onderdonk Avenue, Queens, NY
726582f-a.text:
1416 Flushing Ave. (in front of house seen in foreground), between Onderdonk Ave. (right unpaved) and Seneca Ave.; showing in a set of three views the rear of the Onderdonk-Schoomaker house. Mrs. Ann Onderdonk and her heirs were the owners from 1852-1869. View No. 2 also shows ships on Newtown Creek. View No. 3 shows a 5-story building of the Steel and Tube Inc. of New York in Eings County. The right background is in Queens County. Fore more data see the N.Y. Sun, February 18, 1939.
1922.
Views 1 & 2.
View 3: April 1929.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

726589f-a.text:
